11 law enforcement agency, or local law enforcement agency who is
12 involved in the detention, seizure, or embargo;
13 is immune from civil liability for the detention, seizure, or embargo.
14 (h) The state seed commissioner may order a hemp crop that is
15 detained, seized, or embargoed for noncompliance with this chapter to
16 be destroyed by the owner. However, except as prohibited by federal
17 law, the grower may appeal to the state seed commissioner for the
18 hemp crop to be diverted to a willing licensed processor for processing
19 and sale for industrial use. A hemp crop that is detained, seized, or
20 embargoed may not be used for cannabidiol, other extracts, oil, food,
21 or cosmetic products that are used for humans or animals.
22 (i) A grower shall reimburse the state seed commissioner for the
23 cost of testing conducted on the grower's crop under this section.
